  "text": "Microstructure of mayonnaise samples was observed using a microscope equipped with digital camera (Olympus DP12, B41TF, Japan). A drop of each sample was placed on a microscope slide. Pictures of the mayonnaise microstructure were obtained at the magnification of 40× by a digital camera connected to the microscope [CITATION_1] ). The mean particle diameter of each sample was calculated by using Image J software (1.43 u).",
